<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Relevancy on 08-30-2000 10:41 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I have an idea to make dungeons duable.

Make GROUP quests.
Have X npc hand out "Group" quests,  the quest is dependent on the lvl of the group.
to complete the quest you go to x dungeon and kill x mobs, these mobs drop lore items that you bring back for a REAL amount of experience.  Make to loot drop based on the lvl. IE if a character out of the lvl range kills the Mob the loot does not drop, also the item can not be looted by some one not in the group.  Make the entire group be there when the quest is given, and the entire group come back upon completion.  The reward would have to =  not excede the reward for camping said dungeon.

Do NOT make the quest a 10 zone event, sorry but that is not the sort of thing a viable group will be able to accomplish,  unless of course they play 10 hours a day.

I think also to stop camping VI needs to look at the loot that is dropped.  Make the "item" equivelent to the lvl of the group that can take the monster, not 10 lvls lower.  Ie  what is the point in going to runneye to get the bibs when you already have the giagantic zwiehander?  the only thing to do with it is to sell it.  

Normally, in my experience &lt; that is only 2 months, but...&gt; the items you get from the mobs you can group and kill are not as good as what you have already purchased.  

I say make the items equal to the mob and make them no drop.  who cares about how many of any item are in the game if they can not be sold.  ther would be no profit in some one camping an item forever just for the loot.  make the drops all lvl relative, ie you can not bring your lvl 5 friend in with invis and diamond skin to loot that no drop item that you have to be lvl 20 - 35 to get.  because it is just not there for someone not in the lvl range.

&lt;shrugs&gt;  logistically unrealistic ideas
way to much recoding to do but, it would work, to make the game more interesting and more fun.  as when you wanted X item it did not take days of going to the place and finding it camped by people that do not even get exp for killing the mob (


Runteater
20 Troll Shaman
</TEXTAREA>
